   <narrative xml:lang="EN">.This, coupled with the absence of agricultural risk transfer systems, a difficult trading environment or the main agricultural commodities (in particular sugar) means that the livelihood of small-scale farmers &#x2013; and the associated socio-economic conditions of households in farming communities and Belize in general &#x2013; is highly vulnerable shocks as evidenced by a 2019 drought. The drought, which impacted the sugarcane belt during the first half of 2019, is reported to have been the most intense since 1981.</narrative>
